Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Uyo Zonal Office, have arrested the Director and Project Manager, Akwa Ibom State Action Committee on AIDS, Dr Nkereuwem Etok Akpan, for allegedly embezzling N30 million meant for outreach, sensitisation, HIV testing/ counselling and purchase of screening and confirmatory test tiebreaker.  The suspect was arrested at the weekend following intelligence gathering on how he allegedly misappropriated the said fund, which was paid to the agency in November 2018 by the Office of the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Akwa Ibom State.  According to a statement by the anti-graft agency, investigation into the matter revealed that within the same month the money was released to the agency; Akpan single-handedly instructed that N24, 600,000 be moved into the First City Monument Bank (FCMB) account of a company called Effective Medical Lab belonging to his accomplice, Peter Uduak. Uduak in his statement admitted that he received the said money on the instruction of the suspect, Nkereuwem Etuk Akpan and also withdrew same and handed over to the suspect.  He further stated that he got N100, 000 only from the entire transaction.  “It was also discovered that immediately the money hit Uduak’s account, he withdrew the money between November 26 and November 28, 2018, and handed it over to Akpan in cash, who in turn deposited N22 million into his private account, Life Link Specialist Laboratory, domiciled in Access Bank.